{
  "doc_id": "37570",
  "text": "As far as the factors influencing PrRP are concerned, electroacupuncture (EA) [CITATION_1] and sodium tanshinone IIA sulfonate (STS) [CITATION_2] significantly increase the blood level of E 2 and the expression of PrRP in the medulla oblongata of ovariectomized (OVX) rats. The number of PrRP immunoreactive neurons was higher in the OVX group submitted to EA than that in the control OVX group. The mechanism underlying the ability of EA and STS to improve conditions in reproductive disorders induced by ovariectomy in rats is related to the modulation of blood E 2 levels and the expression of PrRP in the medulla oblongata [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
